{{Infobox religious building | building_name = Emamzadeh Haroun-e-Velayat | infobox_width = | image = | caption = | map_type = Iran | map_size = 275 | location = [[Isfahan]], [[Iran]] | coordinates = {{coord|32.665833|51.682778|display=inline,title}} | religious_affiliation = [[Shia Islam]] | rite = | region = | state = | province = [[Isfahan Province|Isfahan]] | territory = | prefecture = | sector = | district = | cercle = | municipality = [[Isfahan]] | consecration_year = | status = | functional_status = | heritage_designation = | leadership = | website = | architecture = yes | architect = | architecture_type = [[Imamzadeh]] | architecture_style = [[Isfahani style|Isfahani]] | general_contractor = | facade_direction = | groundbreaking = | year_completed = | construction_cost = | specifications = | capacity = | length = | width = | width_nave = | height_max = | dome_quantity = | dome_height_outer = | dome_height_inner = | dome_dia_outer = | dome_dia_inner = | minaret_quantity = | minaret_height = | spire_quantity = | spire_height = | materials = | nrhp = | added = | refnum = | designated = }} '''Emamzadeh Haroun-e-Velayat''' ({{lang-fa|امامزاده هارون ولایت}}) is an [[imamzadeh]] in [[Isfahan]], [[Iran]]. It is located opposite [[Ali minaret]] and belongs to the [[Ismail I]] era. There are many relations about the person, who is buried in it. Some say that he is [[Ja'far al-Sadiq|the sixth Imam]]'s son and some others say, he is [[Ali al-Hadi|the tenth Imam]]'s son, but aside from the matter, who is buried in it, it is the most important historical structure related to the early [[Safavid dynasty|Safavid era]]. Beyond the [[tomb]] it has also a [[portico]], a [[tile]]d [[dome]] and a large yard. It seems that some repairments and improvements have been done in the [[Fath-Ali Shah Qajar|Fath-Ali Shah]] era.<ref>{{cite book|title=Rāhnamā ye Safar be Ostān e Esfāhān(Travel Guide for the Province Isfahan)|publisher=Rouzane|isbn=964-334-218-2|author=Hosseyn Yaghoubi|edit